From Alias to Album - ‘Never On Sunday’ is out now! 
Featuring vocals from Karina Mia and remixes from @orbital, @skreamizm, @krdetroit & P41. We’re excited to finally bring this record to you. 

Available now. Link in our bio.

#octaveone #electronicmusic #techno #newalbum #detroittechno

Price We Play feat. @imkarinamia 🖤 Our new album is out now! 

#electronicmusic #octaveone #detroittechno

So what do you do when you drop a new album? Pack up the cases and hit the road of course! Lots of new N.O.S. tour dates announcing soon. In the next few months we’re hitting Cali & Bogota, Detroit, Croatia (city TBA), Amsterdam, Chicago, and California. Details in bio and ticket links on octaveone.com . We have plans for Paris, London, Mallorca, Berlin, Barcelona, Bordeaux, Lyon, lots more to be announced for later this year. Let’s do this!

Don’t be afraid to experiment and sometimes fail!

Full Video on YouTube: Octave One Point Blank Masterclass
#octaveone #techno #electronicmusic #synthesizer #drummachine #liveset
4 weeks until we're back in Detroit. Countdown to @movementdetroit begins.

Thanks for all the support and love for the new album. 🖤 'Never On Sunday' was originally an alias with @imkarinamia that evolved into an album in its own right. It's up on all digital platforms now if you haven't heard it yet!

#electronicmusic #octaveone #detroittechno

The energy of the moment, that’s really what dance music is about. "We started the original concept to explore non-dance electronic music. Basically it was the music we did we were just messing about with strange ideas. The first Never On Sunday record was done for @carlcraignet’s now defunct Retro-Active record label. @marckinchen was on the A-Side of the record. We were the inner band B-side, which was cool, because this really is the kind of music you need to discover. Produced solely for the sake of art." - In conversation with @psychedelic_baby_magazine

How’s your weekend going? 
We’re finally back in the lab setting up the @rolandglobal MC-707. Been watching the man himself @rudiman.shawn bang on this box for awhile 😄. Looking forward to seeing what secrets lie beneath. 
Also finally recording some tracks that we’ve been deconstructing and reconstructing in the live set. And we’re test driving some new merch for the 2024 launch of the merch line. Managed to also squeeze in a photo session for a talk we did with @resident_advisor that should be dropping soon 😉. In a few days it’ll be time for another airplane ✈️.

✈️ The Mothership has landed back in Europe for @jaegeroslo in Norway tonight! Then onto Switzerland for @electron_festival on Saturday. 

Next week - Poznan, London & Lyon!

Octave One, part of Detroit’s second wave of techno since the late ‘80s, credits their towering live act and revered back catalog to “happy accidents.”

Since their 1989 debut, they’ve stayed relevant, defying categorisation and trends, spreading the Octave One gospel worldwide with an impressive all-hardware live setup.

Before their set at Shi Fu Miz, Adam Wright sat down with the brothers for dumplings and Tsingtao beer, commemorating their first time in Hong Kong as a duo.

“We just made music. And then people started calling us legends, but we’d never thought about it that way.”

From talking about humble beginnings ad first encounters with the likes of Derrick May to their take on the current state of the techno scene, read the entire conversation via our linkinbio.
